messages.content: After an indeterminate amount of time, Morise strolls in with Vega over their shoulder. They place Vega in a room and lock the door, grinning. *Should I do an evil laugh? Probably not.*
Vega realizes she isnt on the comfy bed now and wakes up and starts crying
"Vega please shut up." Morise mutters to themself. "I'm soundproofing that room!" they yell, and stalk away, glowering.
She keeps crying "I WANT NICE LADY!!!! BRING ME BACK!" She sobs
Morise rolls their eyes and walks back to the door. "In a week or something! Vega I need to get some things under control, and the sooner you help me out here, the sooner you can go back!"
"NO YOUR A MEAN PERSON! I WANNA SLEEP ON THE COMFY BED!"
"What the hell is going on?!"
"I snagged a past experiment and she won't *shut up* Binyamin *please make her shut up*."
Shes trying to make more noise by crying and screaming
"Y-you what?!"

(Huamn age is 8
(Mun age is uh.....idk....)
(Young.)
((probably 800,000 then
((still young as shit for muns
(Yeah

"Come on, we're getting Polaris back to the Plasma Zone™️. If Shale starts that bloody revolution we're going to need muns incapacitated or on our side." Morise beckons with a finger and starts to head off.
//can plasma... like, make things out of thin air?
((probably))
Binyamin makes a cuddly doll appear in front of vega, along with placing a soft bed for vega to lay on. Then he follows Morise. "Why do we need Polaris?"
She....doesnt stop though. She doesn't like where she is
"He's one of the mun's more powerful figures, and we just do, okay? Let's go."
"Can't we tell him to come here?"
"No. Let's go, for gods sake."
"...Fine."
Morise nods, and uses their teleportation system of sorts to head to #polaris-and-malachites-house
Binyamin teleports as well.
Shes stopped screaming due to hiw it hurts her throat
Binyamin waits here for Morise.
Shes still crying though
Morise teleports in. "Yo."
Shes hissing now
He shoves Morise as hard as he can. "What's wrong with you?! Taking a kid, and knocking someone out with a shovel!"
"And? I really don't see what's wrong with that. It was necessary." Morise puts Polaris in a separate, more secure, room.
"Necessary?! He was going to come with us willingly! What are you thinking?!"
"That person? Malachite? Dangerous. He threatens *everything* we worked for with Polaris. I couldn't allow them to talk more. Not after trying to tear them apart."
"Yeah, and now they know something's up!"
"What is your problem, Morise?"
"Problem? I don't have a problem." Morise turns and smiles. "I just think logically."
"L... LOGICALLY?! Have you no sense of deceny?!"
"I have nothing to do with that word." Morise shrugs. "I have no morals either."
"..." He takes a deep breath, and punches Morise.
((Morise punch counter: 2))
Morise rolls their eyes. This one affected them more, but. "Come on. We have visitors." She starts to walk towards the #chamber-of-the-elder-plasma
He reluctantly follows.

"Uugh.." Polaris groans, turning onto his back and trying to open his eyes. *Where the fuck...* he thinks, unable to finish the thought. He's too tired, too out of it. He can't remember what happened. "What the fuck...?" Molaris groans out again, sitting up.
Vega is just crying still
"..." his eyes widen as they focus, realizing... he's not home anymore.
"What the f—" he shuts up at the sound of someone crying.
"..." he summons Star Platinum, sending the stand to wherever the sound is. It's difficult to get him there, but soon enough he finds the room were the crying is coming from.
The young mun noticed the stand and freaked out, cowering in fear
"*..Hello?*" Polaris speaks through Star, the stand slowly going onto its knees at the sight of the mun.
"*Hello there. My name is Polaris— what's your name, kiddo?*" he asks, still confused and barely lucid, but trying his best to be kind to the scared mun.
He himself was scared— but there's no time for that.
"Ve-vega....." She sniffled, getting a bit closer
"*Vega, huh? That's a nice name. Are you ok?*"
She shook her head "Sc-scared....wanna go back to nice lady...."
"*Hm... I'm sorry to hear that. Would you like a hug?*" Star sat down with its legs criss cross, holding out its arms wide, but not too wide, offering a hug.
She inched closer before hugging the stand, a small pet rat appearing on her head out of nowhere
Star eyes the animal, but doesn't say anything. "*You seem to think fondly of the nice lady... would you like to tell me about her?*"
Polaris didn't like talking so much, especially right now, but... god, how old was this kid? How did they get here? How did *he* get here?
"Sh-she gave me a nice warm place to sleep....gave me a bath and really yummy food! B-but when I was sleeping after the bath and on the comfy bed....someone took me away..." She sniffled
"..." Polaris was quiet. This mun.. she was taken... Polaris must've been kidnapped, then. He's getting somewhere.
"*I'm sorry about that... Would you like me to stay here with you? I'll keep you safe. You can even sleep on me— my scarf is very warm. Warm enough to be a comfy blanket.*"
She sniffled again but eventually nodded. "Th-thank you...."
He willed Star to smile, small but.. at least something. "*Of course. Keeping people safe is practically my job.*"
Once Vega was asleep, wrapped the young mun in its scarf, plugging her ears and with his fingers, cupping them with the rest of his hand and blocking out all sound.
Polaris stood up, walking up to what he could *assume* was the door, and he let out a long breath.

Without Star, he probably can't do anything— but he doesn't want to leave that child alone, so he's gonna have to do this without it. He reeled his fist back, clenching his teeth, and *slamming* his fist against the door.

He left a small dent, barely noticeable but still there, but god *damn* did that fucking *hurt.* He grunted lowly upon impact, holding his fist to his chest and putting pressure on the knuckles, muting the pain ever so slightly. "*Fuck.*"
Maybe he could...
Nope. Too drained to warp— maybe in a few days he'd be able to warp a little but, but for now.. nothing. Fuck. Fuck. Fuck. *Fuck.*
He kept his temper cool— didn't want to accidentally make Star crush Vega's head.

He took out a deep breath and reeled back his fist again, "**ORA!**" he bellowed, slamming his fist into the material even harder this time, leaving a bigger dent, but not by much. "*GGHK—*" they groaned at the aftermath of the punch, their fist beginning to bleed. "*God* fucking *damnit,*" he bit his lip.
He couldn't do this. Maybe with Star, but without... *Fuck—* everything would be so much better if he could just *remember* what the hell happened. At least then he'd have some closure.
He was panicked— biting back a strong oncoming panic attack. He couldn't panic. There was a kid here, he didn't wanna freak her out— she's freaked out enough already.
*Wait.* Idea.
"..." he looked around, as if someone might be watching, and he took a deep breath, preparing himself.
"**ときょとまれ**." Time stopped.
No time to think— gotta do this quickly. He summoned Star Platinum to him, using their combined fists to beat at the door. "オラオラオラオラオラオラオラオラオラオラオラオラ!"
He didn't stop until the door was barley on its hinges, not wanting to risk running out of time before...
Star Platinum quickly retreated back to its previous position, holding the child close to its chest. "*Time moves again.*"
As time resumed and color bled back into his vision, he let out a sigh of relief as he saw how close the door was to being open.

*Come on, one last punch.*
He reeled his bleeding fist back one more time, other hand in front of him, aiming for the weakest part of the door, and slamming the fist into it with a yell, the door breaking off of its hinges and crashing into the adjacent wall.

He internally pumped a fist, letting himself crack out a small smile.
*Holy shit..* he thought to himself, relieved beyond all belief.
(FUCK YEAHHHH)
He ran out, heading to the room where he felt Star's presence, and he had the stand shake Vega awake.
"*Kiddo? Kiddo, please wake up.*"
She woke up with a start "N-No shakey!"
He chuckled from behind the door. "Apologies," he spoke. Not through Star, but through himself. "Kiddo, you wanna see something cool? You ok with a quick loud sound?"
She thought for a bit before nodding

"Great! Watch this, or not, if you don't want to."
Star put Vega down, wrapping its scarf around its neck again and going up to the door, reeling back its fist.
She tilted her head, watching

"オラオラオラオラオラオラオラオラオラオラオラオラ!" it shouted, barraging the door with as many punches as it could muster. The door quickly broke off of its hinges and slammed against the other side of the corridor, just like the last one. Star Platinum looked back at Vega, smiling, before it disappeared and Polaris appeared from around the wall. "Hey, kiddo. Ready to get the hell outta here?"
She was amazed "Woahh....." she stood up and stared at the probably much taller mun

Polaris kneeled down, holding out his hand for the smaller mun to climb onto. *Tiny...*
"Ready? I'm pretty confused myself— lets go get some answers."
She had just realized how tall he was. What was left of her tail went between her legs and slowly shuffled over to him

He somehow realized how nervous she was, feeling the anxiety coming off of her. "Remember Star? The one who you hugged?" He summoned Star again, the stand smiling at her since Polaris wasn't going to.
"Well, he's basically me. I won't hurt you, promise."
She saw Star and relaxed. ".....I have a Star too.....hes my pet rat....!!" She held the pet rat out, smiling a bit
"That's nice— would you like Star to carry you, or me?" he asked, trying to rush things along.Star was actually arguably bigger than Polaris, yet she found his size more comforting... Meh, whatever
She looked between the 2 before going over to Polaris, doing grabby hands
He couldn't help but crack out a small smile. *Cute kid,* he thought to himself, carefully picking Vega up and placing her on his shoulder.
"Hold on, 'cause I'm about to run."
She nodded and held on tightly
Polaris feels her hold on, but is still nervous for her. He has Star hold her up lightly against his neck, running through the #nursery and heading to the #council room.
Morise enters with a dramatic burst through the door. They walk straight past the cell-rooms and lead the way to one of the more luxurious rooms.
((did they ever repair the two doors that polaris completely wrecked w/ star
((Good question- did they?...
((Nah))
Superbia followed Morise, looking around "My My... what happened to those cell-rooms back there ?"
"An escapee. I was going to have guards posted, but we were... distracted at the time." Morise grimaces. "His name is Polaris, a former experiment of mine."
Superbia nodded "Ah, I see, he must be rather strong..." she tilted her head as Morise said *'experiment'*... " Oh, a former experiment you say ? intresting...~"

"He is. There were three experiments... Polaris, Venor, and Vega. Venor was the most successful, as she only has a single emotion now: Fear. I would've liked to monitor her progress but she was broken out, or she did that by herself. Polaris is... pretty much one of the reasons Shale started the revolution. And I had little to do with Vega.." Morise hums quietly.

"Oh my, you are quite the scientist!" she chuckled quietly " A single emotion ?... fascinating... What kind of goal did you want to archieve with polaris ? Why would he be one of the reasons this Shale started this useless rebellion ?" Superbia was captivated by what Morise was saying

"My main goal is to experiment with emotions. Polaris was one of our environmental experiments - We kept him isolated to see how his emotional range would be affected without the other muns. Shale seems to think that its unacceptable to experiment these days." Morise shrugs.

"Oooh, intresting, I do find the experimentations of emotions to be quite entertaining... And well, I guess she just doesn't understand how genius you are! I don't see anything wrong with experimenting in such manners!" she hummed

"I guess she doesn't. It's quite sad, actually. I think she'd be a help to everything I'm working for if she simply understood..." Morise looks 'downcast' for a second before unlocking a door to a lavish room. "Here you go."

"Ah, unfortunatly, not everyone is cabable of understanding such complex ideas..." she let out  a sigh. After seeing the room, she jumped and giggled, a giant grin on her face "Oh my, such luxury! I wouldn't have expected so much for little old me!"
Morise smiles. "Only the best for my second in command. My own room is adjacent to yours, for means of communication."
Superbia was having trouble hiding her excitement "Well, thank you! and of course, it's better we stay close to communicate faster, I understand"
Morise hums quietly. "You're a smart girl, of course you understand."

((SORRY I LOWKEY FORGOT ZERGD
"I am nothing but the smartest, of course !~" She grinned and  jumped on the bed "It's very comfy as well, perfect!"
((YOU'RE GOOD SGFJHSDKGJ))
"If you do need anything else, don't hesitate to call me... However, for now, I'll be planning or wandering." Morise winks, completely misreading the context of when a wink is supposed to be used.
"Alright, I should be able to entertain myself while you're gone~" She winked back, taking it as it's supposed to, and did finger guns
Morise smiles, nods, and vanishes slowly, only appearing in their room three seconds later.
Superbia took out her tesseracts to read some stuff, and maybe write as well
Morise stands sideways on a wall, pinching the bridge of their nose. "Why am I a *god* to him?" they mumble.
Morise stands in their room and looks at themself in the mirror. "What the hell," they mutter, and lie flat on their bed, staring at the ceiling.

Superbia was finally back in her room, she layed on her bed before noticing Morise's message and screeched ***holy FUCK is this real ?? Am I dreaming***
She was between laughter and pure Joy
Morise stares at the ceiling, flicking an ear only at Superbia's screeching.

She took a deep breath, giggling like an idiot, trying to focus. Surely, Morise didn't seem like the kind to joke like that, or maybe they were ? She's wanted to go and ask them but she was still trying to process *what the FUCK Just happened*

Morise is reading her thoughts silently. *Huh. Interesting.* they think, and thunk their head back onto the bed. Their ceiling is made up of swirling colours and galaxies, by the way - not at all boring.

After a few minutes of flipping the fuck out, Superbia finally managed to calm down, and build up her courage to ask for clarification.
She got up, still a bright smile on her face, humming, and went to knock on Morise's door
"Come in." Morise says, before the knock. Dramatic flair.

She opened to door, and walked in, just a couple of steps, however.
"I... Did you *mean* to send me this message, or perhaps was it a typo ?" Superbia knew this sounded kind of stupid, but she really couldn't believe it.
"You can't typo when you send messages via telepathy." Morise is still staring at the ceiling.

"... Good point" She muttered "So, you meant to send it ? As in, you really do want to date me ?"
She had the biggest grin on her face, her hands behind her back.
"Of... course?" Morise sits up specifically to tilt their head.

She let out a small, quieter screech, and Bounced, smiling. "Oooh my ! I'd never even thought this day would come ! I will not lie, this was a surprise, I did not expect things to move this fast, but I feel like i'm heaven now !" She started to turn around on herself, looking at the ceilling
Morise snorts, amused. "I see."
She turned to Morise and got closer to them "Sooo, when will our first date be ? And where ? What should we do ?" She was giggling
"I don't know. I've never been in a relationship before, you choose." Morise tries a smile.
She gasped "You *never* were in one ? My my, I'll have to try my hardest as I'm your first ! Really surprises me, with how stunning you are"
"Why thank you." Morise grins, lifting their chin to the side. They think they're getting the hang of this.
"Oh, no problem !" She winked "Is there anything like a Nice restaurant around here ? A Nice diner with some candles to light it up would be a pretty Good choice, it's a classic"
"I can make one?" Morise raises a hand in a gentle motion, ready to Thanos Snap a diner into existence.
"wow, wow, no need to make one out of the blue ! ~ I can cook something and decorate a cute little table" She was humming
"If you want." Morise folds their legs and puts their hand down.
She clapped her hands happily, smiling "Great ! I will shop for what is needed, and set it all up, nothing's better than a Nice home cooked meal ~"
Morise smiles at her. "Sounds nice."
"Anything you would like to eat in particular, dear ?" Superbia is making her first attempt at being slightly more casual.
"I normally eat whatever Aemilius leaves in the fridge, so I'd be interested in whatever you enjoy." Morise slides off the bed and stands up.
She chuckled "Alright then~ I'll think up what I can cook, and different decorations, and placement..." She was getting lost in her thought thinking about what she could do
"Alright." Morise stretches their arms because that's what they do.

Superbia was take out of her thought staring at Morise, to her, all of their forms were pretty 
"So, what do you plan on doing now ?"
"Uh. I normally stare at the roof or read." Morise shrugs.
"Ah, I see, life must be quite tranquil for a Plasma, we can fill this void of time with time sent together~" She chukled, humming
"Indeed." Morise chuckles along. Their laughter is like clear bells, very different to their evil cackling.
Superbia sighed, smiling, clearly, Morise was perfect in *every* way to her "I love the way you laugh" She said that without much thoughts.
Morise laughs again. "Thank you. I like your laugh too."
Superbia blushed, surprised but the compliment "Aw, thank you, you're so sweet..." She giggled looking directly in Morise's eyes
Morise looks back and their heterochromatic ((I apologize I love that word and will use it every time I can)) eyes glow a little bit more.
"I really need a map to navigate your eyes. Their glow is so beautiful" She put her hands on her cheeks and Just kept staring.
The line goes over Morise's head but they smile all the same, gliding forward a little closer to Superbia. "They naturally do this..."
Superbia's face Just get brighter with yellow as Morise got closer "That's.... Pretty awsome...and Just pretty in general"
"You blush a lot." Morise comments as they stop just in front of Superbia.
Superbia awkwardly laughed and shrugged "Oh ? Really ? I mean can't really control it, can I ? ~"

((I have no idea lmao))
"I suppose not." Morise stands there. They still have no idea what to do.
Superbia got close enough to Morise to lightly kiss their nose and then backed away slowly, staring at them.
Morise blinks. Once. Twice. "Oh." *I guess we are a thing now..* They kiss Superbia's forehead. Advantage of being taller than her.
Superbia smiled and blushed, she wasn't expecting this, for sure. She purred faintly.
Morise smiles with all their teeth. ((As opposed to just their ~~fangs~~ canines))
Superbia gave a wide smile back "I am glad this revoltion is happening, actually. Because Otherwise we might've never started dating like today"
"Probably." Morise tilts their head. "You're right."

She hummed "I'm sure we'll handle these rebels with no problem ~" She stretched her arms a bit
"I honestly don't see why they would hate you"
"Oh, I don't really care if they hate me. We just need to bring them to heel, and there'll be no problem for the next five million years."
She nodded "Oh, surely, but I'm guessing being a ruler who's loved is Nice. Well, you got me at least~"
"I do." Morise smiles, placing a hand on Superbia's shoulder.
Superbia smiled, purring happily "Indeed, we can always count on eachother ~"
Castus was asleep here

She giggled and this time kissed Morise's cheek.

The first thing he sees is 2 plasma having fun

She looked around, blushing, and stayed silent *what is going on, who's 'Castus'?*
"Stay." Morise surges out into the hallway.
Superbia stayed there, silent
Morise folds their arms. "Castus."
"Am I intruding?"
"What do you think?"
...he scurries out

"Castus. Pucci in the human world. I have no idea where else to put him."
"Oh, I see" She sighed again, looking at the ceilling "Well, at least he's another one of our allies"
"Yeah.." Morise stands there, looking at Superbia. They are not particularly skilled in the art of conversation, in case you haven't noticed.

Superbia streched, and looked at Morise again "Say, Morise, tell me more about yourself, what do you like to do? what passionate you? favorite color? I want to know more about the person I am dating ~"
"I like shapeshifting, I suppose. Lifting weights sometimes. My favourite colours are dark blue and gray."
"Intresting ! so you're the sporty type? Personally, I love red, it's such a pretty color !" she hummed
"I... am, I suppose." Morise has never thought of it that way. They flex an arm. "Red is a pretty colour..." They point to the roof, and swirls of red integrate themselves in the colours.
She stared at Morise's arm for a bit before looking up "Oooh, this is so pretty... you can really create anything just like that ?"
"I can, within the Plasma Zone™️. The Plasma zone™️ works in mysterious ways. My main ability is air manipulation and shapeshifting." Morise trails off, thinking.
"Oh, fascinating" she stared in Morise's eyes again "you truly are amazing, like the moon amongs the stars"
"Heh." The ceiling changes to a scattering of stars, following along with Morise's thoughts.
Knock knock
Superbia turned her head instantly, slightly annoyed *"Is it him again?"* she muttered
Hamichi stood behind him nervously
"What." Morise says icily.
"We have someone who wishes to stay here."
Hamichi looked out from behind Castus, waving a small bit
"Who is it?" Morise unconsciously pulls Superbia closer to them.
"A mun by the name Hamichi. Poor thing lost her memories."
Superbia blushed lightly "Oh, the poor thing did ?" she had a mocking tone
"Lost her memories, or *'lost'* her memories?" Morise rolls their eyes.
"Y-you dont did to call me a poor thing...." She frowned, staring at Castus
"You wish to stay here, do you not?"
She nodded "I-I do....."
Superbia gave a slightly creepy smile "Say, Morise, what do you think about this? Should we allow this *poor soul* to stay ?"
"J-Just because I lost my memories doesnt mean Im a poor soul......." She mumbled, tail flicking in annoyance
"I don't know... She may be useful in the long term..." Morise tilts their head and turns to Superbia. "What's your opinion... dear?"
She giggled " I suppose if she *does* ant to join, we should allow her, darling"
"I agree." Morise smiles at her, then back at the two. "There are some extra sleeping quarters down there. Castus, please escort her." They wave a hand regally.
"As you wish." he escorts her
Superbia yawned and walked out, blowing a kiss to Morise "I'm going to go shopping a little, I'll see you later Dear~"
"See you, then." Morise blows one back, having no idea what that means.

Morise ignores everything to go wash off all this blood.
He noticed, but didn’t bother to ask, this was probably normal, plus he didn’t want to waste energy or time at the moment
Morise returns about five minutes later, then sighs and heads back to Chamber. "Blood, damage." They mutter under their breath.

“another one of the revolution? God how many do they have” he sighs

"Yeah. She got food, I think."
Morise floats over to Superbia's room and opens the door with an extra arm, morphing it seamlessly back into their normal form as the door swings open. They gently lie Superbia down on the bed.
Superbia slightly wiggle in the bed, smiling and whispering a small "thank you" to Morise
Morise smiles slightly and steps away to head out.
There's a shimmering glimmer and a dark shadow ducks behind a wall. *Seriously? Here. Fucking. Here of all places.* Black Orchid is here, and she's  *pissed*.
Superbia was finally waking up. She got up from her bed and stretched, yawning.

Morise is standing by the doorway. "Welcome to the land of the living and the awake." They say, mildly amused. 

Black Orchid hears voices and hisses, ducking down. She gathers a small ball of light in her dark hands.
Superbia chuckled and walked to Morise, hugging them, still a bit sleepy "Morning Dearest"

"Good morning." Morise wraps their arms around Superbia's waist.

Black Orchid releases the ball of light and it gently floats towards the two, invisible.
"I had a very nice dream, did you even sleep ?" She hummed

"I hardly ever sleep." Morise shrugs.

The balls hits the two, releasing its... fusion energy? I guess that's what I'm calling it now.
Superbia barely even noticed it at first and was kind of half asleep in Morise's arms "I feel... Weird"

"I... Yeah." Morise blinks and holds Superbia closer.

*"Annnd... bam."* Black Orchid whispers, and fuses the two together.
Superbia blinked *what the... This feels weird... What's happening ??*
Morise flails one pair of arms. *I.. don't know.* They blink their set of eyes rapidly. *Where did you go?*
Superbia looked around, trying to move the other pair of arms *I don't know... Where are **you**?*
*What. I'm right here.* Morise looks around and nearly falls over, off balance. "What do you.... That is *not my voice*."
She try to lean on a wall, confused "Wait... *oh my god*" *are we.... One person ?!*

"It... seems so." Morise takes one pair of hands in their own and notices they still see when they close their eyes. "....Our consciousnesses are individual, though." *Maybe if we relaxed about it, it'd be easier? Or then we'd just be one person so...* Their thoughts are at a million miles an hour.

Her appetite for chaos apparently unsatisfied, Black Orchid goes off to make more trouble.

Superbia tried to move around, losing her balance once or twice, trying to make sense of how it works "uh...Wack" *I could get used to this. It's not so bad. I miss your touch, tho* She was weirded out by the situation, and had a *lot* of questions, but seemed more relax.
Morise holds Superbia's designated hands with theirs. *Is this better?*
She smiled *perfect. Now let's try to get use to it and find **how** this happened*
*Do you have a mindscape? It may be easier to chat there.* Morise suggests
*well yes, I don't go there that much, but yes* she replied
*I see.* Morise closes their eyes. *If you would allow me...?*
*but of course* she smiled
The fusion, or Suprise, as they've called themself, rejoins the world. "Huh." It's a weird feeling.
They tried walking around, having a way better balance than before "*nice*" they could get used to this
Suprise rolls their first pair of shoulders and grins. "Not bad." Now... Superbia had wanted... breakfast? They head off to the fridge.
Once they were at the fridge they opened it up and grined "Perfect !" they took a piece of Pizza that was here. Breakfast Pizza
Suprise wolfs down the pizza. A very good breakfast indeed. Now, was there anything else Morise or Superbia had needed done?
((Their simp side is coming out))
Suprise put one of their finger to their chin, thinking *what else would be needed ?* they couldn't came up with anything but... An idea *Shapeshifting*
It should be plausible, with Morise's abilities... They take one hand and use one of Morise's favourite tricks, lengthening the nails, just to see if they can.
As the nails got longer, Suprise cackled, *Oh Nice*. They tried to make it as long as possible. Just so see what would happen
They're full on claws by now. Suprise raises an eyebrow as they instinctively retract them - Must be Morise's training.
With their new shapeshifting powers confirmed, Suprise wanted to try a thing : *they focused to have wings*

*Why did Morise never think of this before?* It works pretty well. Suprise notes it down for later; Hopefully Superbia or Morise will remember. *Now... Can they fly. That is the question.* They try them out.
They moved their wings and managed to fly a little over the ground, a bit clumsily. It was... *hard*
"Woah-" They scrape a foot across the ground and Morise blinks dizzily. *I appear to have regained consciousness.*
They soon were back on the ground, Superbia blinking as well *Oh hey Morise*
*Hey. Do you think we can unfuse- I'm slightly disorientated.* Morise admits.
*We can certainly try, I guess* she shrugged
